{
  "stem": "19690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was Orthodox, but we had an organ.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I always remember the cantor had a button by his dais, and the organ was upstairs in the back.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And whenever he wanted the organist to play something, he would push the button.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it would be-- run a-- ring a buzzer upstairs to start the organ.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The rabbi later became our teacher when we couldn't go to school with the Germans anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he became our teacher for all the classes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the cantor would do some of the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] religious school assignments for us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But the rabbi was the most dominant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The synagogue-- we had about 100 families in the-- in Speyer at that time when I was little.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then gradually, they dwindled [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as people left the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And it got less and less.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But in the beginning, we could fill the temple very nicely.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The synagogue was about a 10-minute walk from our house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And of course, no cars in those days to go to temple.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was a walk in and a walk back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And on Yom Kippur, we would do it twice because we always took a break in the afternoon so that my grandfather and my grandmother could break fast for half-day fasting.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we would go home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then usually, my father would stay the whole day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "My father originally, when he was younger, wanted to become a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But he had no voice, same as I have no voice.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And as a result, he became a very frustrated rabbi.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And every now and then, when they needed a fill-in, he was always happy to fill in as a reader, or Torah reader, or whatever, and was very capable at it.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
